cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.DC. 

The paper proposes the use of machine learning, specifically neural net classifiers, to learn the mapping between uncertainty realizations and the active set of constraints at optimality in the optimal power flow problem. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem also involves control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.DC), as well as neural networks (cs.NE) as the specific type of machine learning algorithm used.
